'''Ezroy Millwood''' (1942 – 1 December 2012), was president of [[Jamaica's National Transport Cooperative Society]] (NTCS). He sued the government for breach of its franchise agreement and was awarded more than $1.8 billion in damages. In June 2012, the [[Court of Appeal]] granted the government the go-ahead to challenge the award before the [[British Privy Council]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Transport tycoon dead|url=http://jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20121202/lead/lead21.html|publisher=The Gleaner News|accessdate=7 December 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Ezroy Millwood found dead|url=http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/latestnews/Ezroy-Millwod-found-death|publisher=Jamaica Observer|accessdate=7 December 2012}}</ref>  He was later found dead at his home in [[Saint Andrew Parish, Jamaica|St Andrew]], near Kingston.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ezroy Millwood is dead|url=http://go-jamaica.com/news/read_article.php?id=41480|publisher=Go Jamaica News|accessdate=7 December 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Foul play ruled out in Ezroy Millwood's death|url=http://www.rjrnewsonline.com/local/foul-play-ruled-out-in-ezroy-millwoods-death|publisher=RJR News|accessdate=6 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=No pay, no play - Transport, NTCS heading for new clash over licensing fees - Talk to my lawyers, says Millwood|url=http://mobile.jamaicagleaner.com/20091016/business/business1.php|publisher=Jamaica Gleaner|accessdate=6 June 2018}}</ref>



